Pier, Thank you for sending us the deck for Brachytix. In reviewing your company, we were encouraged by: - Your mission. - The completeness of your team. - The clarity of your explanation of the business. Unfortunately, we're not going to pursue discussions at this time for an investment. Not because it's not promising, but because it's simply not the right fit for [FIRM] at this time. We typically do not invest in hardware businesses. We have invested in the past and have found these ventures to be slower to grow, requiring a lot of capital and usually without network effects (which is our core thesis). Of course, we might be making a mistake in choosing not to continue discussions... that happens. Seeing so many talented teams, we are certainly missing opportunities here. It might help to know that we have to decline 99.6% of the companies we see.
